  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rehabilitation of Agropastoralism at Saint-Jean du Sud</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Besides the socio-economic instability, farmers in the area of Saint-Jean-du-Sud have seen their plantations devastated by many hurricanes and floods. For this reason, farmers need new animals and seeds to give them hope and a better future. This project will provide 100 beef cattle, three cebu bulls, 50,000 cuttings of sweet potatoes, 50,000 cuttings of elephant grass, 20,000 seedlings of fruit trees, 1000 kg of corn , 800 kg of beans, and 80 kg of vegetable seeds. The 200 families&#x2014;100 original families and another 100 benefitting from passing on the gift&#x2014;will be trained on Heifer cornerstones, animal husbandry, sustainable agriculture, and protection of the environment.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Livestock diversification and management, agriculture, agroecological gardens.</narrative>
  </description>
